{"name":"Power Maul (Low)","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Power mauls are elite weapons in many fighting formations, where their club-like form can blow apart reinforced hab doors or crack open armour. Even unpowered, these heavy devices can knock a heretic senseless. This weapon has two entries in the weapons table, representing its two power settings: high and low. Switching the power maul between its two settings is a Free Action. This is a onehanded melee weapon, but when used with two hands it gains the Concussive (0) quality.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":3.5,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+1","damageType":"energy","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Shocking","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/flanged-mace.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1RMHlH5TiB8Ctpd6"}
{"name":"Power Fist","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p><span dir=\"ltr\" style=\"left: 106.514px; top: 784.662px; font-size: 12px; font-family: sans-serif; transform: scaleX(0.736211);\">Power Fists add the user&rsquo;s SB&times;2 to the damage.</span></p>\n<p>One of the most devastating melee weapons in the 41st Millennium, a power fist encloses the user&rsquo;s own hand with a huge mechanical glove complete with articulated fingers. The entire device is sheathed in a power field generated from a source mounted on a backpack or contained within heavy armour, allowing the weapon to crush tank hulls and tear apart barricades. Many are relics dating back centuries, with each user&rsquo;s accomplishments and lineage carefully enscrolled upon the outer surface.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":13,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10","damageType":"energy","penetration":"9","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Power Field, Unwieldy","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/mailed-fist.svg","effects":[],"_id":"29cWI0J4Vgob3M0b"}
{"name":"Power Axe","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p><span dir=\"ltr\" style=\"left: 95.0416px; top: 742.782px; font-size: 12px; font-family: sans-serif; transform: scaleX(0.734273);\">Weapon is Two-Handed</span></p>\n<p>A common weapon amongst the followers of the Machine God, a power axe combines the heavy striking power of an axe with an energy field. While less artful than a power sword, many prefer its devastating attack that few can withstand. A power axe is a two-handed melee weapon.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":6,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+7","damageType":"energy","penetration":"7","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Power Field, Unbalanced","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/sharp-axe.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6HMOiVgkeuB7UtVX"}
{"name":"Power Shield","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>When encased in a power field, these large shields offer excellent protection against attacks that would rip apart mundane armours. Ordo Malleus Inquisitors and their Acolytes often adorn their power shields with heraldry showing the foes banished back to the Warp and other previous victories. A power shield adds 4 Armour points to the wearer&rsquo;s Body and the Arm holding the shield.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":6,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10","damageType":"energy","penetration":"1","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Defensive, Power Field","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/shield.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6r6ofSeb5wQYhwuY"}
{"name":"Ghostblade","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>In the aftermath of Imperial Compliance, Core Theta&rsquo;s Magi took it upon themselves to create a facsimile of the mysterious phase swords of the Callidus Assassin Temple. Never able to truly replicate the design, and lacking an example to study, the final weapon is dangerous to both its user and victim. When a ghostblade Overheats, it is damaged and counts as a regular sword until repaired. Its weight includes the backpack power supply.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":6,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+5","damageType":"energy","penetration":"6","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Felling (4), Razor Sharp, Overheats","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/relic-blade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"AI3VFWqUqvjFvAdl"}
{"name":"Power Maul (High)","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Power mauls are elite weapons in many fighting formations, where their club-like form can blow apart reinforced hab doors or crack open armour. Even unpowered, these heavy devices can knock a heretic senseless. This weapon has two entries in the weapons table, representing its two power settings: high and low. Switching the power maul between its two settings is a Free Action. This is a onehanded melee weapon, but when used with two hands it gains the Concussive (0) quality.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":3.5,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+5","damageType":"energy","penetration":"4","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Power Field, Shocking","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/flanged-mace.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Ae2qDmidcUeBU9DS"}
{"name":"Omnissian Axe","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p><span dir=\"ltr\" style=\"left: 95.0416px; top: 742.782px; font-size: 12px; font-family: sans-serif; transform: scaleX(0.734273);\">Weapon is Two-Handed</span></p>\n<p>Granted to suitably-devoted followers of the Omnissiah, this weapon has a long staff-like body tipped with half of the circular Adeptus Mechanicus skull and cog icon. The symbol forms a blade, and is sheathed in a power field. Covered with inscribed circuitry designs indicating its sacred nature, many a foe has realised far too late that what appeared to be a religious walking staff was really a deadly weapon. An Omnissian axe also functions as a combi-tool and is a two-handed melee weapon.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":8,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10+4","damageType":"energy","penetration":"6","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Power Field, Unbalanced","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/sharp-axe.svg","effects":[],"_id":"OcVOriwTOQ8BAsVb"}
{"name":"Power Sword","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Power swords are a sign of prestige within the Imperium, and many officials without skill wear one in public simply to demonstrate stature. Some of these weapons are handed down as heirlooms, carrying the family name across generations from battle to battle. Power swords come in many styles, allowing for a wide variety of fighting disciplines depending on the blade and its user.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":3,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+5","damageType":"energy","penetration":"5","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Balanced, Power Field","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/croc-sword.svg","effects":[],"_id":"PunvFPf8zhyOwCaS"}
{"name":"Ordo Malleus Power Glaive","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Whilst the hammer may be the symbol of the Ordo Malleus, its agents must stand ready to face a variety of foes, some of them too fast for the sluggish swings of a crackling thunder hammer. The power glaive, a weapon longer than a man is tall, features an elegant silver blade and a haft warded against the corrupting influence of the Warp. An Ordo Malleus power glaive grants the wielder an additional +10 bonus to Parry tests, and is a two-handed weapon.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":4.5,"class":"melee","type":"","range":3,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+8","damageType":"energy","penetration":"5","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Balanced, Power Field, Proven (4), Sanctified","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/glaive.svg","effects":[],"_id":"QwP5n3AFDB4nf2bD"}
{"name":"Thunder Hammer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Thunder hammers incorporate large capacitors that constantly build a charge that is violently released on impact. As the symbol of the Ordo Malleus, thunder hammers are more than just weapons&mdash;they are a badge of office, and a symbol of their unending struggle against the Dark Gods of Chaos. A thunder hammer is a one-handed weapon, but it inflicts an additional +2 damage when used with two hands.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":16,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10+4","damageType":"energy","penetration":"10","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Concussive (2), Power Field, Unwieldy, DMG+2*SB","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/thor-hammer.svg","effects":[],"_id":"V5qWaTYSoTaVYWMC"}
{"name":"Desoleum Power Blade","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>This blade is a small but lethal power weapon that attaches to an easily concealable, spring-loaded wristband. It is popular among gang leaders and assassins alike. This blade is a power weapon and thus requires the Weapon Training (Power) talent. It has the Compact modification (see page 162 of the Dark Heresy Core Rulebook).</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":2,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+3","damageType":"energy","penetration":"5","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Power Field","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/relic-blade.svg","effects":[],"_id":"c67jyob6gZXkLpZa"}
{"name":"Graviton Hammer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A somewhat unusual melee device, this weapon is the result of near-heretical experimentation on Core Theta to incorporate graviton technology into personal combat. Many are passed down from Inquisitor to Inquisitor as a rite of ascension for Acolytes within the Askellon Sector. The graviton hammer is a two-handed weapon.</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":8,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10+5","damageType":"impact","penetration":"7","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Concussive (3), Graviton","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/warhammer.svg","effects":[],"_id":"lKRWBHdjZNCrpmmL"}
{"name":"Power Stake","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Cast from a single rod of blessed iron and featuring a compact power field generator, a power stake is most efective when plunged into the heart of a heretic psyker. Covered in etchings and runes that protect against the machinations of the Warp, it uses the victim&rsquo;s own psychic potency against himself. A power stake inlicts an additional 1d10 Energy damage for every point of psy rating the target possesses. Additionally, possessing a power stake grants a +10 bonus to all Interaction tests made with those aligned with the Ordo Hereticus.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":1,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+7","damageType":"energy","penetration":"5","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Power Field, Sanctified, Unbalanced","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/crystal-wand.svg","effects":[],"_id":"n4F8wV25KmBJ2IRq"}
{"name":"Ebenus Hammer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Also known as the Black Maul, this peculiar weapon has a roughhewn haft of reinforced obsidian and a squarish head made from a rare, light-absorbing metal. Originally wielded by Inquisitor Actius, the youngest of the conclave and a man with little patience for psykers, Ebenus drains nearby Warp energy giving its wielder a significant advantage against psychic foes and the daemonic.</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":16,"class":"melee","type":"","range":0,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10+6","damageType":"energy","penetration":"10","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Daemonbane, Power Field, Unwieldy, DMG+2*SB","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Meele/warhammer.svg","effects":[],"_id":"nKior1gHExye9m0R"}
